Kowloon is a terraced delta city where the Jhen River empties into Coppersalt Bay, north of the continent.
Originally a stilt settlement called the Shallow Thousand, maintained by Lampkeeper hermits who ran oil beacons.
Founded after the Ashfall Monsoon, three years of volcanic rain from the Cinderteeth Mountains that destroyed the delta settlements.
The Neon Covenant, inked in phosphorescent squid dye, established the city's founding law among six surviving houses.
Five governing seats: Harbor Syndics (docks, tariffs), Jade Magistracy (tax, civil law), Temple Circle (healing, sanctuary), Wardens of Iron (walls, militia), Courier Lantern Office (census, signals).
Civic color system: crimson (emergency), jade (permits, magistrate), gold (licensed merchants), blue (harbor), violet (night markets), cyan (floodlines, couriers).
Four named gates: Jade Gate (north, highland trade), Iron Gate (south, wetland frontier), Lantern Gate (west, pilgrim paths), Tide Gate (east, harbor and sea).
The rumored Black Ledger, sealed in a flooded cistern, may contain the unredacted founding census and records of transfers to the Spirebound Conclave.
Annual Ashfall Vigil: all lights extinguished for one hour at midnight, then restored with three strikes on the covenant stone.
